  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nUsing a disk-based database engine like leveldb or peeble is not practical when using it on k8s pods, that normally do not have writable and durable filesystems. Using a remote key/value database like Redis is most effective in this use-case.\r\nOld [issue for Redis](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/2690) has already been opened before and closed without any solution.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nI already implemented the solution, and it should be revised (PR soon), using `db.engine` flag (created for `peeble` usage) to select Redis as the engine. The code is createtd on `rawdb` package, using `ethdb.KeyValueStore` interface.\r\n",
